# Cursor IDE Rules for Maser Media Agency Website Design

## HTML Standards
- Use semantic HTML elements for better accessibility and SEO.
- Ensure HTML is valid and well-structured (use validators).

## CSS Architecture
- Follow BEM (Block Element Modifier) methodology for class naming convention.
- Organize styles into separate files/modules for components, layouts, and utilities.
- Use a CSS preprocessor (like SASS or LESS) to maintain clean and scalable styles.

## Brand Colors
- Primary Color: #004080 (Deep Blue)
- Secondary Color: #FFCC00 (Gold)
- Accent Color: #FF6600 (Vibrant Orange)
- Text Color: #333333 (Dark Gray)
- Background Color: #FFFFFF (White)

## Responsive Design
- Implement media queries to ensure the design adapts to various screen sizes.
- Use a fluid grid layout for flexibility across devices.
- Test responsiveness on multiple devices and browsers to ensure consistency and performance.

## Development Best Practices
- Write clean, maintainable, and well-commented code.
- Use version control (like Git) for tracking changes and collaboration.
- Optimize images and assets for faster load times.
- Conduct regular code reviews and pair programming sessions to maintain code quality.